From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000036 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Sun, 6 Jul 2026 19:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: btbcm: treat 43:30:A0 as a BCM4330 default bdaddr

The Nexus Q's BCM4330B1 powers up reporting BD_ADDR 43:30:A0:00:00:00 --
a waiting-for-configuration placeholder that differs from the
43:30:B1:00:00:00 (BDADDR_BCM4330B1) signature btbcm already knows. Since
it wasn't recognised, btbcm_check_bdaddr() never set HCI_QUIRK_INVALID_BDADDR,
so hci_bcm never set HCI_QUIRK_USE_BDADDR_PROPERTY, and the DT
`local-bd-address` (the real per-device MAC f8:8f:ca:20:49:e5) was never
programmed -- the controller kept the non-unique, group-bit-set placeholder.
Add the 43:30:A0 placeholder to the default-address list so the DT address
is applied via the vendor Write_BD_ADDR at setup.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btbcm.c
@@ -28,6 +28,10 @@
 #define BDADDR_BCM43430A1 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0xaa, 0xaa, 0xaa, 0xaa, 0xaa, 0xaa}})
 #define BDADDR_BCM4324B3 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0xb3, 0x24, 0x43}})
 #define BDADDR_BCM4330B1 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0xb1, 0x30, 0x43}})
+/* steelhead BCM4330B1 reports 43:30:A0:00:00:00 as its unconfigured
+ * placeholder (differs from the B1 signature above); treat it as a
+ * waiting-for-configuration default so the DT local-bd-address is applied. */
+#define BDADDR_BCM4330A0 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0xa0, 0x30, 0x43}})
 #define BDADDR_BCM4334B0 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0xb0, 0x34, 0x43}})
 #define BDADDR_BCM4345C5 (&(bdaddr_t) {{0xac, 0x1f, 0x00, 0xc5, 0x45, 0x43}})
 #define BDADDR_BCM43341B (&(bdaddr_t) {{0xac, 0x1f, 0x00, 0x1b, 0x34, 0x43}})
@@ -126,6 +130,7 @@
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM2076B1) ||
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM4324B3) ||
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM4330B1) ||
+	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM4330A0) ||
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM4334B0) ||
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM4345C5) ||
 	    !bacmp(&bda->bdaddr, BDADDR_BCM43430A0) ||
